  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Learning & Development Specialist",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Design learning and development plans that align organizational capabilities with business needs and strategic objectives</li><li>Execute learning and development programs and channels to build targeted employee skills and competencies</li><li>Leverage emerging learning technologies and channels to enhance program delivery and engagement</li><li>Collaborate with stakeholders to develop future skills maps for various roles, ensuring workforce readiness</li><li>Source and implement group-wide executive education programs for senior management, including certifications and strategic partnerships</li><li>Track, analyze, and report training metrics and KPIs to evaluate the impact and return on investment of learning initiatives</li><li>Manage training initiatives and timelines through effective project management practices</li><li>Interpret training data to inform data-driven decisions that optimize learning outcomes</li><li>Foster positive working relationships and collaborate across teams to support organizational learning goals</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Human Resources, Business, Psychology, Management, or related field</li><li>Minimum of 5 years of proven experience as a learning specialist, training coordinator, or similar role in corporate learning and development</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Strong organizational and time management skills to ensure efficient execution of training programs</li><li>Analytical mindset to interpret training data and support continuous improvement</li><li>Excellent team collaboration skills to establish positive working relationships across organizational levels</li></ul>",
